Priya joined the DAO expecting chaos. She got spreadsheets. The proposals were dry: 'Allocate 2,000 USDC to marketing.' But then someone proposed funding a water filtration project in rural Maharashtra using on-chain voting. Priya wrote the counter-proposal herself: triple the budget, add accountability milestones, publish receipts on-chain. It passed 71%. She hadn't cried at a blockchain vote before. She did that night.

